<p>either on account of provincial taste or ruinous price, is seldom met with.<br/>We went to one shop in particular answering to the above description, &amp; run by a family of people who had lost their home owing to the war.  There were three <strike>old</strike> women, evidently sisters, a younger lady the daughter of one of them &amp; a husband, all Belgians.  The three elderly ladies run the refreshment side while the daughter speaks excellent English &amp; does all the work including a certain amount of cross talk with facetious soldiers while pa looks on &amp; smokes his pipe.  For all the work he does he might just as well be sitting</p>
